assignments.title: ASVAB Test for Juniors and Seniors
assignments.description:
Our school has booked the ASVAB testing date for Friday, April 8, from 7:20 a.m. - 10:20 a.m.
 
The ASVAB test is a tool that identifies one’s interests and skills, helping students explore their options and make a plan for after high school. ASVAB stands for the Armed Services Vocational Aptitude Battery and was originally designed to predict future academic and occupational success in the Military. It’s now used to assess strengths and success in a wide variety of occupations. I believe that students benefit from active career exploration. All students can use the ASVAB as a career planning resource to help explore multiple paths, such as college majors, vocational licensure programs, and the Military. It’s a respected test and there’s no fee or obligation.
 
Participation: The testing is geared toward students in grades 11 and 12. If you choose to take the test, the results are reported to you and PHS guidance and career counselors only. It is the computer-adaptive version and you must bring your Chromebook. If you wish to voluntarily participate, please respond to this email by Friday, April 1, to book a space in the Career Center.
